<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1936#">Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1936</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_63.2-1936"/><heading><desig>§ 63.2-1936.</desig><title>Procedures for posting security, bond or guarantee to secure payment of overdue support</title></heading><bodyText><p>The Department shall require, if feasible and consistent with guidelines established by the Department, that the noncustodial parent post security or bond or give some guarantee to secure overdue payments. Advance notice shall be sent to the noncustodial parent setting forth (i) the amount of the delinquency, (ii) the proposed action to be taken by the Department, (iii) the method available for contesting the impending action and (iv) that only a "mistake of fact" as defined in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 63.2-1900"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1900">§ 63.2-1900<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1900#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> may be contested.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1986, c. 594, § 63.1-250.4; 1988, c. 906; <citation normalizedCite="2002 VA CH 747"><content><span normalizedCite="2002 Va. Ch. 747">2002, c. 747<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2002#000747#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></ci